Current flow in plain English

When a user enters the LOA 1.5 [Level of Assurance 1.5] remote proofing flow, the app calls:

determineVerificationMethod(PersonVo personVo)

This loads the proofing level and sponsor, then calls the deeper overloaded method to select the phone verification supplier. The code comment says this method must only be called once for a user going through the LOA 1.5 flow.  ￼

Inside the main method, it builds a list of possible supplier IDs:

Equifax IDFS OTP
Equifax DIT SMFA
LexisNexis RDP OTP
Experian CrossCore

Then it removes an excluded supplier if one was passed in.  ￼

After that, there are two paths.

Path 1: Normal phone verification path

This is the main COA [Change of Address] issue path.

If the person is not in the LexisNexis Individual Not Found or Experian Customer Not On File retry path, the code does this:

boolean isSwitchingConfigured = isSwitchingConfigured(level, sponsor.getSponsorId());
List<RpOtpAttemptConfig> list =
    otpAttemptConfigService.getByProofingLevelSorted(...);
selectedSupplier = selectSupplier(personVo, level, list);

￼

That getByProofingLevelSorted query comes from RpOtpAttemptConfig. It selects from rp_kba_attempts, filters by proofing level, sponsor, supplier IDs, and totalAttempts <> 0, then orders by:

attempts ASC,
supplierId DESC

So the supplier with the lowest current ATTEMPTS is picked first. If there is a tie, higher supplier ID wins because of descending supplier ID.  ￼

Then selectSupplier(...) loops through that sorted list:

for (RpOtpAttemptConfig att : list) {
    if (att.getAttempts() < att.getTotalAttempts()) {
        chosen = att;
        break;
    }
}

If all suppliers already reached their configured total, it picks the first row in the sorted list. Then it calls:

updatePvAttempts(personVo, level, chosen);

￼

That is the hot spot.

